The Special Investigating Unit says the scale of PPE corruption is bigger than any other it's uncovered before. eNCA's Govan Whittles has the details. #DStv403​ #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The Special Investigating Unit (SIU) says R13.3 billion worth of government Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) expenditure is subject to investigation. READ: WATCH: SIU releases findings of investigations into PPE tender fraud SIU head ADV. Andy Mothibi says 26-percent of the entire investigation is finalised.  Up to R13.3-billion worth of government personal protective equipment expenditure is subject to investigation by the SIU. #DStv403​ #eNCA R13.3-billion worth of government PPE expenditure is subject to investigation by the SIU. The SIU head says 26-percent of the whole investigation has been finalised. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/sAcuEp4rb1 Mothibi also says political pressure is just one of the reasons that played a role in the awarding of PPE tenders. Some companies were decided upon even before the supply chain management process started. Watch the video above for more details on this story.